<item>
            <title>[AMQ-1777] Access to ConnectionEventListeners in RA&apos;s ActiveMQManagedConnection is not synchronized</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-1777</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the RA&apos;s connection to the broker fails and the &amp;lt;i&amp;gt;ActiveMQManagedConnection.onException()&amp;lt;/i&amp;gt; method is called, all the registered &amp;lt;i&amp;gt;ConnectionEventListener&amp;lt;/i&amp;gt;s are notified.&lt;br/&gt;
At least in Glassfish, the registered listener then calls the &amp;lt;i&amp;gt;ActiveMQManagedConnection.removeConnectionEventListener()&amp;lt;/i&amp;gt; to unregister itself. This causes a &amp;lt;i&amp;gt;java.util.ConcurrentModificationException&amp;lt;/i&amp;gt; to be thrown since the &amp;lt;i&amp;gt;ConnectionEventListener&amp;lt;/i&amp;gt; collection is modified while the &amp;lt;i&amp;gt;onException()&amp;lt;/i&amp;gt; iterates over it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Kai&lt;/p&gt;</description>
